<span class="displaytext"><h4><a href="/iowa/">john(candidate last).com/iowa</a> gives voters direct link to campaign in their area</h4> <p><b>des moines, iowa</b> – the (candidate full) for president campaign today released a website specifically for iowa's first-in-the-nation caucus goers. the web site, <a href="/iowa/">www.john(candidate last).com/iowa</a>, provides iowans with information on how to get involved in the campaign as well as details on (candidate last)' bold and specific plans on issues from iraq to universal health care. it also tracks john and elizabeth (candidate last) travels throughout iowa and it will include pictures and video of their discussions with everyday iowans. </p><p>"iowa is the first stop in our drive to change america—and success here is going to be critical," said (candidate last). "elizabeth and i have had many opportunities to visit with iowans over the past few years, but this web site will give iowans the chance to learn more about my plans for bold change. most importantly, it is a tool that will help iowans get involved in the important challenges facing our country today." </p><p>the iowa website—which will be regularly updated—includes: </p><p></p><ul> <li>news from the campaign trail</li> <li>pictures and video of john and elizabeth (candidate last) as they visit with iowans</li> <li>downloadable fact sheets and other items so that caucus goers can learn about (candidate last)' positions on the issues—and then share that information with friends and neighbors</li> <li>a six minute video detailing (candidate full) plan for universal health coverage</li> <li>lists of upcoming events</li> <li>many ways to get involved, including registering as a supporter of the campaign, offering to volunteer, and an email feature allowing iowans to invite friends and family to visit the site and learn more about the campaign</li> <li>a page allowing caucus goers to get in contact with the nearest campaign office</li> </ul> <p>additional features and information will be added throughout the campaign, and (candidate last) invited iowans—whether they are already supporters or still undecided—to check back at the page frequently to hear the latest news from the campaign. </p><p>(candidate last) recently completed his 22nd trip to iowa since 2004 and will return on may 15th.</p></span>



